This includes extensions to the AToM MIB defined in RFC 2515 to allow statistics retrieval as well as extensions to the ILMI link attributes. Copyright 2003-2011 Alcatel-Lucent. All rights reserved. AtmConnectionOwner.name: AtmConnectionOwner
AtmConnectionOwner.description: This texual convention identifies the system entity that owns a specific ATM connection.

AtmOamStatus.name: AtmOamStatus
AtmOamStatus.description: This texual convention indicates the OAM operational status of ATM connections. Ete indicates end to end connection. Ais denotes alarm indication signal and Rdi is for remote defect indication. Loc indicates the alarm was due to loss of continuity.

AtmIlmiStatus.name: AtmIlmiStatus
AtmIlmiStatus.description: This textual convention indicates the ILMI status of the VCL or VPL. If through ILMI an operational condition or misconfiguration has been detected, tAtmVclInfoIlmiStatus or tAtmVplInfoIlmiStatus will reflect this condition.

AtmLlid.name: AtmLlid
AtmLlid.description: This texual convention is the 16 octets that identifies the system Loopback location Id (LLID). As required by the ATM OAM Loopback capability. This texual convention is defined in ITU-T standard I.610.

AtmIlmiLinkUniType.name: AtmIlmiLinkUniType
AtmIlmiLinkUniType.description: AtmIlmiLinkUniType is an enumerated integer whose value indicates ATM UNI type.

AtmIlmiLinkDeviceType.name: AtmIlmiLinkDeviceType
AtmIlmiLinkDeviceType.description: AtmIlmiLinkDeviceType is an enumerated integer whose value indicates the advertised device type.

AtmIlmiLinkVersion.name: AtmIlmiLinkVersion
AtmIlmiLinkVersion.description: AtmIlmiLinkVersion is an enumerated integer whose value indicates the ILMI version of either `3.0', `3.1' or `4.0' that is advertised by IME.

AtmIlmiLinkImeType.name: AtmIlmiLinkImeType
AtmIlmiLinkImeType.description: AtmIlmiLinkImeType is an enumerated integer whose value indicates the ILMI IME type of either `User-Side' or `Network-Side'.

tAtmMdaInfoTable.name: tAtmMdaInfoTable
tAtmMdaInfoTable.description: The tAtmMdaInfoTable contains ATM MDA status information. This table is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAtmMdaInfoEntry.name: tAtmMdaInfoEntry
tAtmMdaInfoEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmMdaInfoEntry containing status information applicable to an ATM MDA. This entry is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVpcs.name: tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVpcs
tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVpcs.description: The value of tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVpcs indicates the maximum number of ATM VPCs that can be configured on this MDA. This object is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVccs.name: tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVccs
tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVccs.description: The value of tAtmMdaMaxSupportedVccs indicates the maximum number of ATM VCCs that can be configured on this MDA. This object is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAtmMdaConfiguredVpcs.name: tAtmMdaConfiguredVpcs
tAtmMdaConfiguredVpcs.description: The value of tAtmMdaConfiguredVpcs indicates the number of ATM VPCs that have been configured on this MDA. This object is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAtmMdaConfiguredVccs.name: tAtmMdaConfiguredVccs
tAtmMdaConfiguredVccs.description: The value of tAtmMdaConfiguredVccs indicates the number of ATM VCCs that have been configured on this MDA. This object is obsoleted in release 3.0.

tAtmIntfConfTable.name: tAtmIntfConfTable
tAtmIntfConfTable.description: The tAtmIntfConfTable contains ATM interface configuration and status not included in the AToM MIB definition in RFC 2515.

tAtmIntfConfEntry.name: tAtmIntfConfEntry
tAtmIntfConfEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmIntfConfEntry containing additional configuration and status information applicable to an ATM interface.

tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVpcs.name: tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVpcs
tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVpcs.description: The value of tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVpcs indicates the maximum number of VPCs that may be currently configured on this ATM interface. The value is the minimum of atmInterfaceMaxVpcs, and the atmInterfaceMaxVpcs of the interface's UNI/NNI peer as negotiated by ILMI. If the interface does not negotiate with its peer to determine the number of VPCs that can be configured on the interface, then the value of this object must equal atmInterfaceMaxVpcs.

tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVccs.name: tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVccs
tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVccs.description: The value of tAtmIntfCurrentMaxVccs indicates the maximum number of VCCs that may be currently supported on this ATM interface. The value is the minimum of atmInterfaceMaxVccs, and the atmInterfaceMaxVccs of the interface's UNI/NNI peer as negotiated by ILMI. If the interface does not negotiate with its peer to determine the number of VCCs that can be configured on the interface, then the value of this object must equal atmInterfaceMaxVccs.

tAtmIntfTotalIngrCbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalIngrCbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalIngrCbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalIngrCbrBandwidth indicates the total Cbr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the ingress direction.

tAtmIntfTotalIngrRtVbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalIngrRtVbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalIngrRtVbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalIngrRtVbrBandwidth indicates the total rtVbr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the ingress direction.

tAtmIntfTotalIngrNrtVbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalIngrNrtVbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalIngrNrtVbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalIngrNrtVbrBandwidth indicates the total nrtVbr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the ingress direction.

tAtmIntfTotalIngrUbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalIngrUbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalIngrUbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalIngrUbrBandwidth indicates the total Ubr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the ingress direction.

tAtmIntfTotalEgrCbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalEgrCbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalEgrCbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalEgrCbrBandwidth indicates the total Cbr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the egress direction.

tAtmIntfTotalEgrRtVbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalEgrRtVbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalEgrRtVbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalEgrRtVbrBandwidth indicates tje total rtVbr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the egress direction.

tAtmIntfTotalEgrNrtVbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalEgrNrtVbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalEgrNrtVbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalEgrNrtVbrBandwidth indicates the total nrtVbr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the egress direction.

tAtmIntfTotalEgrUbrBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfTotalEgrUbrBandwidth
tAtmIntfTotalEgrUbrBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfTotalEgrUbrBandwidth indicates the total Ubr bandwidth consumed on this interface in the egress direction.

tAtmIntfBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfBandwidth
tAtmIntfBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfBandwidth indicates the total ATM link bandwidth accepted on this interface.

tAtmIntfShapedBandwidth.name: tAtmIntfShapedBandwidth
tAtmIntfShapedBandwidth.description: The value of tAtmIntfShapedBandwidth indicates the total shaped bandwidth consumed on this interface in the egress direction.

tAtmIntfLastUnknVpi.name: tAtmIntfLastUnknVpi
tAtmIntfLastUnknVpi.description: The value of tAtmIntfLastUnknVpi indicates the last unknown Vpi that was received on this interface.

tAtmIntfLastUnknVci.name: tAtmIntfLastUnknVci
tAtmIntfLastUnknVci.description: The value of tAtmIntfLastUnknVci indicates the last unknown vci that was received on this interface.

tAtmIntfOperStatus.name: tAtmIntfOperStatus
tAtmIntfOperStatus.description: The value of tAtmIntfOperStatus indicates the status of the ATM interface. If the SONET-PATH layer and TC Sublayer are operationally up, the ATM Interface is considered up. If the SONET-PATH layer and/or TC Sublayer is down, the ATM Interface is set to lowerLayerDown.

tAtmIntfConfVtcs.name: tAtmIntfConfVtcs
tAtmIntfConfVtcs.description: The value of tAtmIntfConfVtcs indicates the number of VTCs currently in use at this ATM interface.

tAtmIntfConfIfcs.name: tAtmIntfConfIfcs
tAtmIntfConfIfcs.description: The value of tAtmIntfConfIfcs indicates the number of IFCs currently in use at this ATM interface.

tAtmIntfStatsTable.name: tAtmIntfStatsTable
tAtmIntfStatsTable.description: The tAtmIntfStatsTable contains ATM interface stats at the ATM Layer.

tAtmIntfStatsEntry.name: tAtmIntfStatsEntry
tAtmIntfStatsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmIntfStatsEntry containing statistics information applicable to an ATM interface.

tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsRxd.name: tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsRxd
tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells received by the ATM interface including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsTxd.name: tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsTxd
tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells transmitted by the ATM interface including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells.

tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesRxd.name: tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesRxd
tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesRxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesRxd indicates the number of bytes received on this interface. This is the number of tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsRxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesTxd.name: tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesTxd
tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesTxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfStatsTotalBytesTxd indicates the number of bytes transmitted on this interface. This is the number of tAtmIntfStatsTotalCellsTxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmIntfStatsTotalUnknCellsDrp.name: tAtmIntfStatsTotalUnknCellsDrp
tAtmIntfStatsTotalUnknCellsDrp.description: The value of tAtmIntfStatsTotalUnknCellsDrp indicates the number of cells dropped due to an unknown VPI/VCI.

tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErr.name: tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErr
tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErr.description: The value of tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErr indicates the number of cells with uncorrectable HEC Errors on this interface.

tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErrFixed.name: tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErrFixed
tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErrFixed.description: The value of tAtmIntfStatsTotalHecErrFixed indicates the number of cells with correctable HEC Errors on this interface.

tAtmIntfAal5StatsTable.name: tAtmIntfAal5StatsTable
tAtmIntfAal5StatsTable.description: The tAtmIntfAal5StatsTable contains ATM interface stats at the AAL5 Layer.

tAtmIntfAal5StatsEntry.name: tAtmIntfAal5StatsEntry
tAtmIntfAal5StatsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmIntfAal5StatsEntry containing statistics information applicable to an ATM interface at the AAL5 Layer.

tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsRxd.name: tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsRxd
tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsRxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsRxd indicates the number of AAL5 PDUs that are received by the ATM interface.

tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsTxd.name: tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsTxd
tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsTxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsTxd indicates the number of AAL5 PDUs that are transmitted by the ATM interface.

tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpRxd.name: tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpRxd
tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpRxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpRxd indicates the number of AAL5 PDUs dropped by the ATM interface in the receive direction. This count does not include crc32 Errors or oversized SDU discards

tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpTxd.name: tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpTxd
tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpTxd.description: The value of tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalPktsDrpTxd indicates the number of AAL5 PDUs dropped in the transmit direction. This count does not include crc32 Errors or oversized SDU discards.

tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalCrc32Err.name: tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalCrc32Err
tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalCrc32Err.description: The value of tAtmIntfAal5StatsTotalCrc32Err indicates the number of Errors detected by the 32 bit cyclic redundancy check.

tAtmIfcInfoTable.name: tAtmIfcInfoTable
tAtmIfcInfoTable.description: The tAtmIfcInfoTable contains configuration and status information for ATM interface-level connections.

tAtmIfcInfoEntry.name: tAtmIfcInfoEntry
tAtmIfcInfoEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmIfcInfoTable containing configuration and status information applicable to ATM interface-level connections.

tAtmIfcAdminStatus.name: tAtmIfcAdminStatus
tAtmIfcAdminStatus.description: tAtmIfcAdminStatus specifies the desired administrative state of the IFC.

tAtmIfcOperStatus.name: tAtmIfcOperStatus
tAtmIfcOperStatus.description: tAtmIfcOperStatus indicates the current operational status of the IFC.

tAtmIfcLastChange.name: tAtmIfcLastChange
tAtmIfcLastChange.description: tAtmIfcLastChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time this IFC entered its current operational state.

tAtmIfcReceiveTrafficDescrIndex.name: tAtmIfcReceiveTrafficDescrIndex
tAtmIfcReceiveTrafficDescrIndex.description: tAtmIfcReceiveTrafficDescrIndex identifies the row in the atmTrafficDescrParamTable which applies to the receive direction of the IFC.

tAtmIfcTransmitTrafficDescrIndex.name: tAtmIfcTransmitTrafficDescrIndex
tAtmIfcTransmitTrafficDescrIndex.description: tAtmIfcTransmitTrafficDescrIndex identifies the row in the atmTrafficDescrParamTable which applies to the transmit direction of the IFC.

tAtmIfcRowStatus.name: tAtmIfcRowStatus
tAtmIfcRowStatus.description: tAtmIfcRowStatus indicates the current RowStatus of the IFC. Entries in the tAtmIfcInfoTable are created as a result of the creation of another system entity (such as a SAP). Since entries in this table can not be created directly, tAtmIfcRowStatus is read-only and will always be 'active' if the row exists.

tAtmIfcCastType.name: tAtmIfcCastType
tAtmIfcCastType.description: tAtmIfcCastType indicates the connection topology type.

tAtmIfcConnKind.name: tAtmIfcConnKind
tAtmIfcConnKind.description: The value of tAtmIfcConnKind indicates the use of call control.

tAtmIfcInfoOwner.name: tAtmIfcInfoOwner
tAtmIfcInfoOwner.description: The value of tAtmIfcInfoOwner indicates which application caused the creation of the ATM interface-level connection.

tAtmIfcStatisticsTable.name: tAtmIfcStatisticsTable
tAtmIfcStatisticsTable.description: The tAtmIfcStatisticsTable is used to gather cell-level statistics on a particular IFC entry.

tAtmIfcStatisticsEntry.name: tAtmIfcStatisticsEntry
tAtmIfcStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmIfcStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular IFC entry.

tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsRxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsRxd
tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells received by the IFC including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd
tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells received by the IFC. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsTxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsTxd
tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells transmitted by the IFC including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd
tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells transmitted by the IFC. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesRxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesRxd
tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesRxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesRxd indicates the number of bytes received by this IFC. This is the number of tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsRxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesTxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesTxd
tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesTxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsTotalBytesTxd indicates the number of bytes transmitted by this IFC. This is the number of tAtmIfcStatsTotalCellsTxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmIfcStatsDrpCellsRxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsDrpCellsRxd
tAtmIfcStatsDrpCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsDrpCellsRxd indicates the number of all policer cells discards (CLP=0+1) of the IFC. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd
tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of all policer CLP=0 cells discards of the IFC. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.name: tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd
tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of all CLP=0 cells discards of this IFC. This includes both discards due to buffer management and policer.

tAtmIfcStatsTagCells.name: tAtmIfcStatsTagCells
tAtmIfcStatsTagCells.description: The value of tAtmIfcStatsTagCells indicates the number of tagged CLP=0 cells of the IFC. The egress may or may not discard these cells.

tAtmVclInfoTable.name: tAtmVclInfoTable
tAtmVclInfoTable.description: The tAtmVclInfoTable is used to display non-configuration information on a particular VCL entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAtmVclInfoEntry.name: tAtmVclInfoEntry
tAtmVclInfoEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVclInfoTable containing non-configuration information applicable to a particular VCL entry in the AToM MIB.

tAtmVclInfoOwner.name: tAtmVclInfoOwner
tAtmVclInfoOwner.description: The value of tAtmVclInfoOwner indicates which application caused the creation of the ATM VCL.

tAtmVclInfoOamStatus.name: tAtmVclInfoOamStatus
tAtmVclInfoOamStatus.description: The value of tAtmVclInfoOamStatus indicates the OAM operational status of the VCL.

tAtmVclInfoIlmiStatus.name: tAtmVclInfoIlmiStatus
tAtmVclInfoIlmiStatus.description: The value of tAtmVclInfoIlmiStatus indicates the ILMI status of the VCL.

tAtmVclInfoRxTrafficDescrIdOvr.name: tAtmVclInfoRxTrafficDescrIdOvr
tAtmVclInfoRxTrafficDescrIdOvr.description: This object indicates the index of the ATM ingress traffic descriptor override. This override value is given by an AAA server such as a RADIUS server. The value zero indicates that no override is given.

tAtmVclInfoTxTrafficDescrIdOvr.name: tAtmVclInfoTxTrafficDescrIdOvr
tAtmVclInfoTxTrafficDescrIdOvr.description: This object indicates the index of the ATM egress traffic descriptor override. This override value is given by an AAA server such as a RADIUS server. The value zero indicates that no override is given.

tAtmVclStatisticsTable.name: tAtmVclStatisticsTable
tAtmVclStatisticsTable.description: The tAtmVclStatisticsTable is used to gather cell-level statistics on a particular VCL entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAtmVclStatisticsEntry.name: tAtmVclStatisticsEntry
tAtmVclStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVclStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular VCL entry in the AToM MIB.

tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsRxd.name: tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsRxd
tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells received by the VCL including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsTxd.name: tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsTxd
tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells transmitted by the VCL including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesRxd.name: tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesRxd
tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesRxd.description: The value of tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesRxd indicates the number of bytes received by this Vcl. This is the number of tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsRxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesTxd.name: tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesTxd
tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesTxd.description: The value of tAtmVclStatsTotalBytesTxd indicates the number of bytes transmitted by this Vcl. This is the number of tAtmVclStatsTotalCellsTxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmOamVclStatisticsTable.name: tAtmOamVclStatisticsTable
tAtmOamVclStatisticsTable.description: The tAtmOamVclStatisticsTable is used to gather oam statistics on a particular VCL entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAtmOamVclStatisticsEntry.name: tAtmOamVclStatisticsEntry
tAtmOamVclStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVclStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular VCL entry in the AToM MIB.

tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsTxd.name: tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsTxd
tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsTxd indicates the number of AIS cells transmitted on this VC for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsTxd.name: tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsTxd
tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsTxd indicates the number of RDI cells transmitted on this VC for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsTxd.name: tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsTxd
tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsTxd indicates the number of loopback requests and responses transmitted on this VC for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsRxd
tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVclStatsAISCellsRxd indicates the number of AIS cells received on this VC for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsRxd
tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVclStatsRDICellsRxd indicates the number of RDI cells received on this VC for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsRxd
tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVclStatsLoopbackCellsRxd indicates the number of loopback requests and responses received on this VC for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVclStatsCrc10Err.name: tAtmOamVclStatsCrc10Err
tAtmOamVclStatsCrc10Err.description: The value of tAtmOamVclStatsCrc10Err indicates the number of oam cells discarded with CRC 10 Errors.

tAtmOamVclStatsOtherCellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVclStatsOtherCellsRxd
tAtmOamVclStatsOtherCellsRxd.description: This value of tAtmOamVclStatsOtherCellsRxd indicates the number of oam cells that are received but not identified.

tAal5VccStatisticsTable.name: tAal5VccStatisticsTable
tAal5VccStatisticsTable.description: tAal5VccStatisticsTable is used to gather AAL5-level statistics on a particular AAL5 VCC entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAal5VccStatisticsEntry.name: tAal5VccStatisticsEntry
tAal5VccStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAal5VccStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular AAL5 VCC entry in the AToM MIB.

tAal5VccStatsPacketsRxd.name: tAal5VccStatsPacketsRxd
tAal5VccStatsPacketsRxd.description: The value of tAal5VccStatsPacketsRxd indicates the number of valid AAL-5 SDUs and AAL-5 SDUs with CRC-32 errors received by the AAL-5 VCC.

tAal5VccStatsPacketsTxd.name: tAal5VccStatsPacketsTxd
tAal5VccStatsPacketsTxd.description: The value of tAal5VccStatsPacketsTxd indicates the number of AAL-5 SDUs transmitted by the AAL-5 VCC.

tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsRxd.name: tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsRxd
tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsRxd.description: The value of tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsRxd indicates the number of dropped AAL-5 SDUs that have been received on the AAL-5 VCC.

tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsTxd.name: tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsTxd
tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsTxd.description: The value of tAal5VccStatsDrpPacketsTxd indicates the number of dropped AAL-5 SDUs that would have been transmitted on the AAL-5 VCC.

tAtmCellVclStatisticsTable.name: tAtmCellVclStatisticsTable
tAtmCellVclStatisticsTable.description: tAtmCellVclStatisticsTable is used to gather cell-level statistics on a particular VCC entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAtmCellVclStatisticsEntry.name: tAtmCellVclStatisticsEntry
tAtmCellVclStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmCellVclStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular VCL entry in the AToM MIB.

tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsRxd
tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells received by the VCL.

tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsTxd.name: tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsTxd
tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmCellVclStatsClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells transmitted by the VCL.

tAtmCellVclStatsDrpCellsRxd.name: tAtmCellVclStatsDrpCellsRxd
tAtmCellVclStatsDrpCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmCellVclStatsDrpCellsRxd indicates the number of all policer cells discards (CLP=0+1) of the VCL. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd
tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of all policer CLP=0 cells discards of the VCL. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.name: tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd
tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmCellVclStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of all CLP=0 cells discards of this VCL. This includes both discards due to buffer management and policer.

tAtmCellVclStatsTagCells.name: tAtmCellVclStatsTagCells
tAtmCellVclStatsTagCells.description: The value of tAtmCellVclStatsTagCells indicates the number of tagged CLP=0 cells of the VCL. The egress may or may not discard these cells.

tAtmVplInfoTable.name: tAtmVplInfoTable
tAtmVplInfoTable.description: The tAtmVplInfoTable is used to display non-configuration information on a particular VPL entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAtmVplInfoEntry.name: tAtmVplInfoEntry
tAtmVplInfoEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVplInfoTable containing non-configuration information applicable to a particular VPL entry in the AToM MIB.

tAtmVplInfoOwner.name: tAtmVplInfoOwner
tAtmVplInfoOwner.description: The value of tAtmVplInfoOwner indicates which application caused the creation of the ATM VPL.

tAtmVplInfoOamStatus.name: tAtmVplInfoOamStatus
tAtmVplInfoOamStatus.description: The value of tAtmVplInfoOamStatus indicates the OAM operational status of the VPL.

tAtmVplInfoIlmiStatus.name: tAtmVplInfoIlmiStatus
tAtmVplInfoIlmiStatus.description: The value of tAtmVplInfoIlmiStatus indicates the ILMI status of the VPL.

tAtmVplStatisticsTable.name: tAtmVplStatisticsTable
tAtmVplStatisticsTable.description: The tAtmVplStatisticsTable is used to gather cell-level statistics on a particular VPL entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAtmVplStatisticsEntry.name: tAtmVplStatisticsEntry
tAtmVplStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVplStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular VPL entry in the AToM MIB.

tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsRxd.name: tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsRxd
tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells received by the VPL including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd
tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells received by the VPL. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsTxd.name: tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsTxd
tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM cells transmitted by the VPL including both CLP=0 and CLP=1 cells. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd.name: tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd
tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells transmitted by the VPL. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesRxd.name: tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesRxd
tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesRxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesRxd indicates the number of bytes received by this VPL. This is the number of tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsRxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesTxd.name: tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesTxd
tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesTxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsTotalBytesTxd indicates the number of bytes transmitted by this VPL. This is the number of tAtmVplStatsTotalCellsTxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmVplStatsDrpCellsRxd.name: tAtmVplStatsDrpCellsRxd
tAtmVplStatsDrpCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsDrpCellsRxd indicates the number of all policer cells discards (CLP=0+1) of the VPL. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd
tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of all policer CLP=0 cells discards of the VPL. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.name: tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd
tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of all CLP=0 cells discards of this VPL. This includes both discards due to buffer management and policer.

tAtmVplStatsTagCells.name: tAtmVplStatsTagCells
tAtmVplStatsTagCells.description: The value of tAtmVplStatsTagCells indicates the number of tagged CLP=0 cells of the VPL. The egress may or may not discard these cells.

tAtmOamVplStatisticsTable.name: tAtmOamVplStatisticsTable
tAtmOamVplStatisticsTable.description: The tAtmOamVplStatisticsTable is used to gather oam statistics on a particular VPL entry in the RFC 2515 AToM MIB.

tAtmOamVplStatisticsEntry.name: tAtmOamVplStatisticsEntry
tAtmOamVplStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVplStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular VPL entry in the AToM MIB.

tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsTxd.name: tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsTxd
tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsTxd indicates the number of AIS cells transmitted on this VPL for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsTxd.name: tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsTxd
tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsTxd indicates the number of RDI cells transmitted on this VPL for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsTxd.name: tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsTxd
tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsTxd indicates the number of loopback requests and responses transmitted on this VPL for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsRxd
tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVplStatsAISCellsRxd indicates the number of AIS cells received on this VPL for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsRxd
tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVplStatsRDICellsRxd indicates the number of RDI cells received on this VPL for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsRxd
tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmOamVplStatsLoopbackCellsRxd indicates the number of loopback requests and responses received on this VPL for both end to end and segment.

tAtmOamVplStatsCrc10Errors.name: tAtmOamVplStatsCrc10Errors
tAtmOamVplStatsCrc10Errors.description: The value of tAtmOamVplStatsCrc10Errors indicates the number of OAM cells discarded on this VPL with CRC 10 errors.

tAtmOamVplStatsOtherCellsRxd.name: tAtmOamVplStatsOtherCellsRxd
tAtmOamVplStatsOtherCellsRxd.description: This value of tAtmOamVplStatsOtherCellsRxd indicates the number of OAM cells that are received on this VPL but not identified.

tAtmVtlInfoTable.description: The tAtmVtlInfoTable is used to display non-configuration information on a particular VTL entry.

tAtmVtlInfoEntry.name: tAtmVtlInfoEntry
tAtmVtlInfoEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVtlInfoTable containing non-configuration information applicable to a particular VTL entry.

tAtmVtlStartVpi.name: tAtmVtlStartVpi
tAtmVtlStartVpi.description: The starting VPI value of the VTL.

tAtmVtlEndVpi.name: tAtmVtlEndVpi
tAtmVtlEndVpi.description: The ending VPI value of the VTL.

tAtmVtlAdminStatus.name: tAtmVtlAdminStatus
tAtmVtlAdminStatus.description: tAtmVtlAdminStatus specifies the desired administrative state of the VTL.

tAtmVtlOperStatus.name: tAtmVtlOperStatus
tAtmVtlOperStatus.description: tAtmVtlOperStatus indicates the current operational status of the VTL.

tAtmVtlLastChange.name: tAtmVtlLastChange
tAtmVtlLastChange.description: tAtmVtlLastChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time this VTL entered its current operational state.

tAtmVtlReceiveTrafficDescrIndex.name: tAtmVtlReceiveTrafficDescrIndex
tAtmVtlReceiveTrafficDescrIndex.description: tAtmVtlReceiveTrafficDescrIndex identifies the row in the atmTrafficDescrParamTable which applies to the receive direction of the VTL.

tAtmVtlTransmitTrafficDescrIndex.name: tAtmVtlTransmitTrafficDescrIndex
tAtmVtlTransmitTrafficDescrIndex.description: tAtmVtlTransmitTrafficDescrIndex identifies the row in the atmTrafficDescrParamTable which applies to the transmit direction of the VTL.

tAtmVtlRowStatus.name: tAtmVtlRowStatus
tAtmVtlRowStatus.description: tAtmVtlRowStatus indicates the current RowStatus of the VTL. Entries in the tAtmVtlInfoTable are created as a result of the creation of another system entity (such as a SAP). Since entries in this table can not be created directly tAtmVtlRowStatus is read-only and will always be 'active' if the row exists.

tAtmVtlCastType.name: tAtmVtlCastType
tAtmVtlCastType.description: tAtmVtlCastType indicates the connection topology type.

tAtmVtlConnKind.name: tAtmVtlConnKind
tAtmVtlConnKind.description: tAtmVtlConnKind indicates the use of call control.

tAtmVtlInfoOwner.name: tAtmVtlInfoOwner
tAtmVtlInfoOwner.description: The value of tAtmVtlInfoOwner indicates which application caused the creation of the ATM VTL.

tAtmVtlStatisticsTable.name: tAtmVtlStatisticsTable
tAtmVtlStatisticsTable.description: The tAtmVtlStatisticsTable is used to gather cell-level statistics on a particular VTL entry.

tAtmVtlStatisticsEntry.name: tAtmVtlStatisticsEntry
tAtmVtlStatisticsEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmVtlStatisticsTable containing statistics information applicable to a particular VTL entry.

tAtmVtlStatsTotalCellsRxd.name: tAtmVtlStatsTotalCellsRxd

tAtmVtlStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmVtlStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd
tAtmVtlStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsTotalClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells received by the VTL. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVtlStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsTotalClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of valid ATM CLP=0 cells transmitted by the VTL. If traffic policing is implemented, then cells are counted prior to the application of traffic policing.

tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesRxd.name: tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesRxd
tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesRxd.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesRxd indicates the number of bytes received by this VTL. This is the number of tAtmVtlStatsTotalCellsRxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesTxd.name: tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesTxd
tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesTxd.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsTotalBytesTxd indicates the number of bytes transmitted by this VTL. This is the number of tAtmVtlStatsTotalCellsTxd multiplied by 53.

tAtmVtlStatsDrpCellsRxd.name: tAtmVtlStatsDrpCellsRxd
tAtmVtlStatsDrpCellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsDrpCellsRxd indicates the number of all policer cells discards (CLP=0+1) of the VTL. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.name: tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd
tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsRxd indicates the number of all policer CLP=0 cells discards of the VTL. This excludes any buffer management discards (if applicable).

tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.name: tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd
tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsDrpClp0CellsTxd indicates the number of all CLP=0 cells discards of this VTL. This includes both discards due to buffer management and policer.

tAtmVtlStatsTagCells.name: tAtmVtlStatsTagCells
tAtmVtlStatsTagCells.description: The value of tAtmVtlStatsTagCells indicates the number of tagged CLP=0 cells of the VTL. The egress may or may not discard these cells.

tAtmSysLlid.name: tAtmSysLlid
tAtmSysLlid.description: The ATM LLID is the Loopback location ID that uniquely identifies the system for the ATM OAM Loopback purposes.

tAtmSysOamRetryUp.name: tAtmSysOamRetryUp
tAtmSysOamRetryUp.description: The value of tAtmSysOamRetryUp specifies the number of consecutive OAM loopback attempts that must succeed after the periodic attempt before the endpoint will transition from the eteAisLoc state to up. A value of 0 means that the endpoint will transition to the up state immediately if the periodic loopback attempt succeeds.

tAtmSysOamRetryDown.name: tAtmSysOamRetryDown
tAtmSysOamRetryDown.description: The value of tAtmSysOamRetryDown specifies the number of consecutive OAM loopback attempts that must fail after the periodic attempt before the endpoint will transition from the up state to eteAisLoc. A value of 0 means that the endpoint will transition to the eteAisLoc state immediately if the periodic loopback attempt fails.

tAtmSysOamLoopbackPeriod.name: tAtmSysOamLoopbackPeriod
tAtmSysOamLoopbackPeriod.description: The value of tAtmSysOamLoopbackPeriod specifies the number of seconds between periodic loopback attempts on an ATM endpoint that has periodic loopback enabled.

tAtmIlmiLinkTable.name: tAtmIlmiLinkTable
tAtmIlmiLinkTable.description: The tAtmIlmiLinkTable is used to configure ILMI Link attributes.

tAtmIlmiLinkEntry.name: tAtmIlmiLinkEntry
tAtmIlmiLinkEntry.description: An entry in the tAtmIlmiLinkTable containing additional management information applicable to a particular ILMI link on an ATM interface

tAtmIlmiLinkRowStatus.name: tAtmIlmiLinkRowStatus
tAtmIlmiLinkRowStatus.description: tAtmIlmiLinkRowStatus is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table.

tAtmIlmiLinkLastChanged.name: tAtmIlmiLinkLastChanged
tAtmIlmiLinkLastChanged.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkLastChanged indicates the sysUpTime value when this row was last modified.

tAtmIlmiLinkAdminStatus.name: tAtmIlmiLinkAdminStatus
tAtmIlmiLinkAdminStatus.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkAdminStatus specifies the administrative status for the ILMI Link.

tAtmIlmiLinkOperStatus.name: tAtmIlmiLinkOperStatus
tAtmIlmiLinkOperStatus.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkOperStatus indicates the operational status of the ILMI Link.

tAtmIlmiLinkVpi.name: tAtmIlmiLinkVpi
tAtmIlmiLinkVpi.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkVpi specifies the VPI value of the ILMI link. Once this row has been created, this value cannot be modified.

tAtmIlmiLinkVci.name: tAtmIlmiLinkVci
tAtmIlmiLinkVci.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkVci specifies the VCI value of the ILMI link. This value cannot be zero. Once this row has been created, this value cannot be modified.

tAtmIlmiLinkFsmState.name: tAtmIlmiLinkFsmState
tAtmIlmiLinkFsmState.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Appendix 1
tAtmIlmiLinkFsmState.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkFsmState indicates the state of the ILMI Finite State Machine associated with this interface.

tAtmIlmiLinkReceiveTrafficDescrIndex.name: tAtmIlmiLinkReceiveTrafficDescrIndex
tAtmIlmiLinkReceiveTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkReceiveTrafficDescrIndex specifies the value of the atmTrafficDescrParamIndex index for the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this ILMI link. This value cannot be zero.

tAtmIlmiLinkTransmitTrafficDescrIndex.name: tAtmIlmiLinkTransmitTrafficDescrIndex
tAtmIlmiLinkTransmitTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkTransmitTrafficDescrIndex specifies the value of the atmTrafficDescrParamIndex index for the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the transmit direction of this ILMI link. This value cannot be zero.

tAtmIlmiLinkEstablishConPollIntvl.name: tAtmIlmiLinkEstablishConPollIntvl
tAtmIlmiLinkEstablishConPollIntvl.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.1
tAtmIlmiLinkEstablishConPollIntvl.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkEstablishConPollIntvl specifies the amount of time S, in seconds, between successive transmissions of ILMI messages on this interface for the purpose of detecting the establishment of ILMI connectivity.

tAtmIlmiLinkCheckConPollIntvl.name: tAtmIlmiLinkCheckConPollIntvl
tAtmIlmiLinkCheckConPollIntvl.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.1
tAtmIlmiLinkCheckConPollIntvl.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkCheckConPollIntvl specifies the amount of time T, in seconds, between successive transmissions of ILMI messages on this interface for the purpose of detecting loss of ILMI connectivity. The distinguished value zero disables ILMI connectivity procedures on this interface.

tAtmIlmiLinkConPollInactFactor.name: tAtmIlmiLinkConPollInactFactor
tAtmIlmiLinkConPollInactFactor.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.1
tAtmIlmiLinkConPollInactFactor.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkConPollInactFactor specifies the number K of consecutive polls on this interface for which no ILMI response message is received before ILMI connectivity is declared lost.

tAtmIlmiLinkUniType.name: tAtmIlmiLinkUniType
tAtmIlmiLinkUniType.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.4.1
tAtmIlmiLinkUniType.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkUniType indicates the UNI type of either `public' or `private' to be advertised by ILMI from this end of the interface.

tAtmIlmiLinkDeviceType.name: tAtmIlmiLinkDeviceType
tAtmIlmiLinkDeviceType.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.4.1
tAtmIlmiLinkDeviceType.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkDeviceType indicates the device type of either `user' or `node' to be advertised by ILMI from this end of the interface.

tAtmIlmiLinkVersion.name: tAtmIlmiLinkVersion
tAtmIlmiLinkVersion.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.2.3.13
tAtmIlmiLinkVersion.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkVersion specifies the ILMI version of either `3.1' or `4.0' to be advertised by ILMI from this end of the interface. The configuration of version `3.0' is not allowed.

tAtmIlmiLinkImeType.name: tAtmIlmiLinkImeType
tAtmIlmiLinkImeType.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.4.1
tAtmIlmiLinkImeType.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkImeType specifies the configured IME type of either `User-Side' or `Network-Side'.

tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedVersion.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedVersion
tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedVersion.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.2.3.13
tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedVersion.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedVersion specifies the ILMI version of either `3.0', `3.1' or `4.0' negotiated with peer IME.

tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedImeType.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedImeType
tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedImeType.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.4.1
tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedImeType.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNegotiatedImeType specifies the resulting IME type of either `User-Side' or `Network-Side' based on local and remote UNI type and device type.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborIfIdentifier.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborIfIdentifier
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborIfIdentifier.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.1
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborIfIdentifier.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborIfIdentifier indicates the interface identifier advertised by the peer IME. A value of 0 indicates that the value has not been received from the peer IME.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborSystemIdentifier.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborSystemIdentifier
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborSystemIdentifier.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.1
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborSystemIdentifier.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborSystemIdentifier indicates The system identifier advertised by the peer IME. A value of `0' indicates that the value has not been received from the peer IME.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborUniType.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborUniType
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborUniType.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.4.1
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborUniType.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborUniType indicates the UNI type of either `public' or `private' that is advertised by the peer IME. A value of `undefined' indicates that the value has not been received from the peer IME.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborDeviceType.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborDeviceType
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborDeviceType.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.3.4.1
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborDeviceType.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborDeviceType indicates the device type of either `user' or `node' that is advertised by the peer IME. A value of `undefined' indicates that the value has not been received from the peer IME.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborVersion.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborVersion
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborVersion.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.2.3.13
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborVersion.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborVersion indicates the ILMI version of either `3.0', `3.1' or `4.0' that is advertised by the peer IME. A value of `undefined' indicates that the value has not been received from the peer IME.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpcs.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpcs
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpcs.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.2.3.4
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpcs.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpcs indicates the maximum number of VPCs that can be supported by the neighbor. If the interface does not negotiate with its peer to determine the number of VPCs that can be configured on the interface, then the value of this object must equal 0.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVccs.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVccs
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVccs.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.2.3.5
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVccs.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVccs indicates the maximum number of VCCs that can be supported by the neighbor. If the interface does not negotiate with its peer to determine the number of VCCs that can be configured on the interface, then the value of this object must equal 0.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpiBits.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpiBits
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpiBits.reference: ATM Forum, Integrated Local Management Interface (ILMI) Specification, Version 4.0, af-ilmi-0065.000, September 1996, Section 8.2.3.2
tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpiBits.description: The value of tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVpiBits indicates the maximum number of VPI bits that can be supported by the neighbor. If the interface does not negotiate with its peer to determine the number of VPI bits that can be configured on the interface, then the value of this object must equal 0.

tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVciBits.name: tAtmIlmiLinkNeighborMaxVciBits
